# UI rules — Meavo design system

Org standard (see STANDARDS.md §5 in meavo-agent-templates). Deviations for this repo are listed at the bottom.

## Components

- Use the in-house kit in `src/components/ui.tsx`: `Card`, `Button` (primary/secondary/danger/ghost), `Input`, `Textarea`, `PageHeader`.
- Do NOT add shadcn, Radix, MUI, or any external component library.
- Top nav and tool switcher come from `@meavo/navigation` — do not build a custom header.

## Palette & visual language

- Primary actions: brand green `bg-brand-600 hover:bg-brand-700` (#30A46C / #0C8F61).
- Neutrals: Tailwind `slate` scale. Errors: `text-sm text-red-600`.
- Cards: `rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white shadow-sm`. Inputs/buttons: `rounded-lg`.
- Page titles: `text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900`. Body: `text-sm text-slate-600`.
- Focus: `focus:ring-brand-100 focus:border-brand-500`.

## Responsive (required on every page)

- Mobile-first: style for narrow viewport, add `sm:` / `lg:` overrides upward.
- Main container: `mx-auto max-w-6xl px-3 py-4 sm:px-4 sm:py-8`.
- Grids: `grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3`.
- Wide tables must degrade on mobile — stacked cards or `overflow-x-auto`, never clipped columns.
- Touch targets ≥ 44px; no hover-only affordances for critical actions.
- Check new pages at 375px and 1280px before opening a PR.

## Rendering

- Server Components by default; `"use client"` only for interactive leaves (dashboards, logger wizards, modals).
- Modals: accessible custom pattern — focus trap, Escape closes, `role="dialog"`.

## Repo-specific deviations

- Dashboard and logger UI strings are **Bulgarian** by design — keep the existing language unless asked.
- The kit has no `Select` component — native `<select>` elements styled inline are the current pattern.
- Field-staff dashboards are heavily mobile-used; treat 375px rendering as a first-class requirement, not a check-box.
